sources.description:
IT’S YOUR OWN ARMY - IN THE ARMY’S OWN SHOW!
A soldier wounded in the War (WWI) becomes a producer and stages a show for the forces.

Director: Michael Curtiz
Writers: Casey Robinson, Claude Binyon

Main cast:
George Murphy - Jerry Jones
Joan Leslie - Eileen Dibble
Ronald Reagan - Johnny Jones
Alan Hale - Sgt. McGee

Genres: Comedy, Musical, Romance, War
Gross Box Office (US & Canada) $20,831,178
Release date: July 14, 1943
Filming location: Burbank, California, USA
